<item>
            <title>[CXF-1609] The setSynchronousTimeout on the ClientImpl does not prevent reading the socket to timeout...</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1609</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This method has apparently been replaced with&lt;br/&gt;
    HTTPConduit.setReceiverTimeout(Long). &lt;br/&gt;
    HTTPConduit.setConnectionTimeout(Long)&lt;br/&gt;
I can&apos;t remember how the old way was meant to work (private void ClientImpl.waitForResponse(...)) but this seems to be deprecated atm.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other thing:&lt;br/&gt;
        HTTPConduit.setReceiverTimeout(Long)&lt;br/&gt;
        HTTPConduit.setConnectionTimeout(Long)&lt;br/&gt;
are casted as int in the conduit :&lt;br/&gt;
        connection.setConnectTimeout((int)clientSidePolicy.getConnectionTimeout());&lt;br/&gt;
        connection.setReadTimeout((int)clientSidePolicy.getReceiveTimeout());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This conversion is very dangerous e.g Long.MAX_VALUE is converted into a negative integer!&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
